EXPECT_BUFFER "sem awgke. "

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Beam decoder: multi-position adjacent-key noise
# (dogfood 2026-07-15: "Mávahlíð er komin á koetip" intending "kortið" —
# e→r and p→ð, two adjacent-key substitutions. The old generate-and-test
# edits2 died inside its budget before reaching it and the bar filled with
# junk splits; the prefix-range beam decodes it in ~2 nats.)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

SCENARIO koetip decodes kortið in icelandic context and auto-applies
T "Mávahlíð er komin á "
EXPECT_POSTERIOR_GT 0.8
T koetip
EXPECT_VERBATIM koetip
# Margins clear organically: kortið (z −0.19, DP cost ~2.05) leads the
# "kost*"-tier runners-up past the ordinary margin, and rewrite distance 2
# keeps it under the far-repair discipline.
EXPECT_AUTOCORRECT kortið
# Saturated-lane split discipline + the beam's cheap repair suppressing the
# split pass: the old "joe tip"/"moe tip" cherry-picked-English junk splits
# are gone at P(IS) = 0.9.
EXPECT_NOT_CONTAINS "joe tip"
EXPECT_NOT_CONTAINS "moe tip"

SCENARIO koetip commits kortið through space
T "Mávahlíð er komin á koetip "
EXPECT_BUFFER "Mávahlíð er komin á kortið "
EXPECT_LAST_COMMIT kortið

SCENARIO eirld decodes world in english context
# Same class, English lane: e→w and i→o. A lone single-indel reading
# ("eiröld") must not suppress the multi-substitution decode (beamDeepGate
# sits below the indel constant).
T "the weather is "
T eirld
EXPECT_AUTOCORRECT world

SCENARIO tonirriw triple noise decodes tomorrow
# Three adjacent-key substitutions (n→m, i→o, i→o) — beyond the old edits2
# entirely. Far-repair discipline allows auto-apply only because tomorrow
# is COMMON vocabulary (z ≥ autocorrectFarRepairMinZ); the awgke scenario
# above locks the mash side of the same rule (rare "aegis" stays bar-only).
T "see you tonirriw"
EXPECT_AUTOCORRECT tomorrow

# ============================================================
# Lane relaxation profiles (PLAN.md "diacritics are an input method, not an
# error"): acute-vowel folds price ~ε inside a saturated Icelandic lane,
# apostrophe folds + lone-i caps mirror it in English; skeleton collisions
# auto-apply past the valid-word rule only through the triple gate
# (dominance × context × deliberateness) plus the sletta guard.
# ============================================================

SCENARIO accent naked sentence restores end to end in icelandic lane
# The headline: a rational fast typist skips the long-press accents and the
# engine restores them. "i" → í (single-letter special case), "bud" → búð
# (u→ú fold + d→ð confusion discount, past EN-valid "bud" via the triple
# gate + sletta guard), everything else already valid.
T "við vorum að versla. "
EXPECT_POSTERIOR_GT 0.75
T "flytjum i bud fyrir helgina "
EXPECT_BUFFER "við vorum að versla. flytjum í búð fyrir helgina "
EXPECT_POSTERIOR_GT 0.85

SCENARIO for restores to fór through the triple gate in a saturated lane
# "for" is a valid word (en.lex + BÍN), so the sacred valid-word rule
# applies — and all gates pass: fór dominates (369k vs a BÍN-only
# skeleton at headline z +1.77), context "ég fór" supports it, no
# deliberateness signal, and the saturated lane overwhelms the English
# reading of "for" (sletta guard).
T "við vorum að versla. ég for"
EXPECT_POSTERIOR_GT 0.85
EXPECT_VERBATIM for
EXPECT_AUTOCORRECT fór
T " heim "
EXPECT_BUFFER "við vorum að versla. ég fór heim "

SCENARIO vist stays offer-only because dominance fails
# víst sits at z +0.78 — below the dominance bar for a BÍN-valid skeleton
# of unknown frequency ("vist" is a real word is.lex never measured).
# Offer-only: both readings visible, nothing auto-applied.
T "við vorum að versla. þetta er alveg vist"
EXPECT_POSTERIOR_GT 0.85
EXPECT_CONTAINS víst
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT
T " "
EXPECT_BUFFER "við vorum að versla. þetta er alveg vist "

SCENARIO vil never steals its rare accent twin
# The ratio machinery proper: vil (178k) ≫ víl (5) — restoration the wrong
# way around must not even come close.
T "við vorum að versla. ég vil"
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT
T " "
EXPECT_BUFFER "við vorum að versla. ég vil "

SCENARIO sletta guard blocks fór at a merely-leaning lane
# P(IS) ≈ 0.71 clears the lane gate but not the sletta guard: the blend
# advantage over the English reading of "for" (z +2.36) stays under the
# threshold — offer-only until the lane saturates.
T "ekki flytjum "
EXPECT_POSTERIOR_GT 0.65
EXPECT_POSTERIOR_LT 0.75
T for
EXPECT_CONTAINS fór
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT
T " "
EXPECT_BUFFER "ekki flytjum for "

SCENARIO english lane leaves for untouched
T "this is for"
EXPECT_POSTERIOR_LT 0.3
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT
T " you "
EXPECT_BUFFER "this is for you "

SCENARIO long-pressed character vetoes folding for the word
# Deliberateness hierarchy, strongest signal: the o was picked from the
# long-press callout, so "for" is exactly what the user meant — fór stays
# offered, never applied, and the literal token commits.
T "við vorum að versla. ég f"
LONGPRESS o
T r
EXPECT_CONTAINS fór
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT
T " "
EXPECT_BUFFER "við vorum að versla. ég for "

SCENARIO long-pressed accent is never folded away
# Exact-input-wins invariant, long-press flavor: a deliberately entered
# accent must never be rewritten to its skeleton (or anything else).
T "við vorum að versla. ég f"
LONGPRESS ó
T r
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT
T " "
EXPECT_BUFFER "við vorum að versla. ég fór "

SCENARIO exact accented input is never restored differently
# Exact input wins by ε: deliberately typed accents are never penalized.
T "við vorum að versla. ég fór heim"
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT
T " "
EXPECT_BUFFER "við vorum að versla. ég fór heim "

SCENARIO personal skeleton vetoes restoration of itself
# The user explicitly learned the skeleton (deliberateness part c):
# personal dict outranks restoration — fór stays offer-only.
PERSONAL for 5
T "við vorum að versla. ég for"
EXPECT_CONTAINS fór
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT
T " "
EXPECT_BUFFER "við vorum að versla. ég for "

SCENARIO tombstoned accented form is never restored to
TOMBSTONE fór
T "við vorum að versla. ég for"
EXPECT_NOT_CONTAINS fór
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT

SCENARIO url field gets no restoration at all
# Field-kind invariant: restoration-class suggestions are dropped, not just
# de-flagged — domains are unaccented by convention.
FIELD url
T "við vorum að versla "
EXPECT_POSTERIOR_GT 0.85
T bud
EXPECT_NOT_CONTAINS búð
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT
T " "
EXPECT_BUFFER "við vorum að versla bud "
FIELD standard

SCENARIO secure field gets no restoration at all
FIELD secure
T "við vorum að versla "
T bud
EXPECT_NOT_CONTAINS búð
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT
FIELD secure
FIELD standard

SCENARIO dont offers don't in an english lane
# EN profile, apostrophe folding: the omitted apostrophe prices ~ε in a
# saturated EN lane. With en.lex v3's repaired contraction counts
# (don't 41.4M on-disk vs the dont skeleton folded to 0 — see
# data/README.md "Contraction frequency repair"), the triple gate passes
# (dominance + context + no deliberateness) and don't AUTO-APPLIES —
# the designed behavior the v2 data was too broken to permit. Escape
# hatch: the verbatim slot is always present. (Veto-asymmetry decision
# 2026-07-16: dead-center taps no longer veto restoration-only winners —
# a careful tap on the base key is the lazy-input signal, not evidence
# against the apostrophe.)
T "and he said why dont"
EXPECT_POSTERIOR_LT 0.2
EXPECT_AUTOCORRECT don't
T " "
EXPECT_BUFFER "and he said why don't "

SCENARIO personal don't auto-restores from dont in an english lane
# Personal vocabulary participates in folded matching: the learned
# contraction outranks the error-class rivals and passes the triple gate
# (dominance: dont is not English vocabulary; sletta guard: its is.lex
# junk-tier reading is overwhelmed in an EN lane).
PERSONAL don't 6
T "and he said why dont"
EXPECT_AUTOCORRECT don't
T " "
EXPECT_BUFFER "and he said why don't "

SCENARIO cant restores to can't under v3 dominance
# en.lex v2 had cant (996k, apostrophe-stripped corpus artifact)
