# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Coordinate-level decoding (PLAN.md "Touch decoding", stage 1): the TAP
# <char> <dx> <dy> directive types one character WITH its touch point
# (within-key normalized offsets, −0.5…+0.5 at the cell edges, x right /
# y down — the extension's action-handler forwarding, verbatim). The
# bidirectional evidence principle end to end: boundary taps ENABLE
# corrections, dead-center taps VETO them, tapless typing is byte-identical
# to the static engine.

SCENARIO dead-center taps veto the koetip auto-apply
# Statically "koetip " auto-applies "kortið" (the beam-decoder dogfood
# case). With every tap dead center the user demonstrably hit exactly
# k-o-e-t-i-p — believe them: the substitutions price near the Gaussian
# exponent of a full key pitch, kortið drops out, nothing auto-applies.
TAP k 0 0
TAP o 0 0
TAP e 0 0
TAP t 0 0
TAP i 0 0
TAP p 0 0
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT
EXPECT_NOT_CONTAINS kortið
T " "
EXPECT_BUFFER "koetip "

SCENARIO boundary taps keep the koetip auto-apply firing
# Same word, but the two noisy positions lean toward the keys kortið
# needs (e→r, p→ð): the neighbor readings become floor-cost and the
# repair fires exactly like the static engine — the margin veto only
# aggregates taps that CONTRADICT the rewrite, and these support it.
TAP k 0 0
TAP o 0 0
TAP e 0.45 0
TAP t 0 0
TAP i 0 0
TAP p 0.45 0
EXPECT_AUTOCORRECT kortið
T " "
EXPECT_BUFFER "kortið "

SCENARIO tap direction disambiguates hestir
# Statically "hestir" ranks gestir (g→h) above hestur (i→u) — both ~1-nat
# static substitutions. A boundary tap on the i leaning toward u makes
# the hestur reading floor-cost, while the dead-center taps everywhere
# else price the rival substitutions near the cap — the tap-supported
# reading leads the bar. (hestir is BÍN-valid, so nothing may auto-apply
# — ranking only.)
TAP h 0 0
TAP e 0 0
TAP s 0 0
TAP t 0 0
TAP i -0.45 0
TAP r 0 0
EXPECT_TOP hestur
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT

SCENARIO dead-center taps demote the substitution readings of hestir
# Same word, all dead center: no substitution reading can be a slip, so
# the indel-shaped hesti (omitted-r) leads and hestur drops out of the
# bar entirely. (gestir stays reachable — the FIRST beam edit allows any
# key up to the cost cap — but only in the tail, never on top.)
TAP h 0 0
TAP e 0 0
TAP s 0 0
TAP t 0 0
TAP i 0 0
TAP r 0 0
EXPECT_TOP hesti
EXPECT_NOT_CONTAINS hestur
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT

SCENARIO tapless typing after tapped words stays static
# TAP evidence is per word: the record retires at the commit, and a
# tapless word behaves exactly like the pre-coordinate engine.
TAP k 0 0
TAP o 0 0
TAP e 0 0
TAP t 0 0
TAP i 0 0
TAP p 0 0
T " koetip"
EXPECT_AUTOCORRECT kortið

SCENARIO backspace retires the tap of the removed character
# Dead-center taps veto kortið; backspacing the p and retyping it
# WITHOUT a tap leaves position 5 static — but positions 0–4 keep their
# dead-center veto, so kortið stays out and nothing auto-applies.
TAP k 0 0
TAP o 0 0
TAP e 0 0
TAP t 0 0
TAP i 0 0
TAP p 0 0
BACKSPACE
T p
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT

SCENARIO touch samples are emitted only for committed as-typed words
# Dead-center taps → "koetip" commits as typed → 1 wordCommitted + 6
# touchSample events (per-key Gaussians groundwork, M2 stage 2).
TAP k 0 0
TAP o 0 0
TAP e 0 0
TAP t 0 0
TAP i 0 0
TAP p 0 0
T " "
EXPECT_LAST_COMMIT koetip
EXPECT_EVENTS 7

SCENARIO corrected words emit no touch samples
# Boundary taps → the kortið auto-apply fires on space → the commit is a
# suggestionAccepted (1 event, no touchSamples: corrected taps were
# errors and must not train the touch model).
TAP k 0 0
TAP o 0 0
TAP e 0.45 0
TAP t 0 0
TAP i 0 0
TAP p 0.45 0
T " "
EXPECT_LAST_COMMIT kortið
EXPECT_EVENTS 1

SCENARIO url fields emit no touch samples
# The hard privacy gate covers coordinates too.
FIELD url
TAP k 0 0
TAP o 0 0
TAP e 0 0
TAP t 0 0
TAP i 0 0
TAP p 0 0
T " "
EXPECT_EVENTS 0

SCENARIO dead-center base-vowel taps keep accent restoration firing
# The fold-composition rule (FoldPricing doc): a dead-center tap on the
# BASE key is exactly the lazy-input signal — confidence ≈ 1 multiplies a
# ≈0 evidence penalty into the fold likelihood, and restoration pairs are
# exempt from the margin veto. The error-class substitutions (bus, bid)
# get vetoed off the bar while búð still auto-restores; the LONGPRESS
# deliberateness veto (previous scenarios) remains the signal that stops
# folding — taps and callouts compose, they do not conflict.
T "hann sagði að við hefðum "
TAP b 0 0
TAP u 0 0
TAP d 0 0
EXPECT_AUTOCORRECT búð
EXPECT_NOT_CONTAINS bus
T " "
EXPECT_BUFFER "hann sagði að við hefðum búð "

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Possessive apostrophe restoration (EN profile, derived possessives —
# 2026-07-16 contraction_damage wave). en.lex carries almost no possessive
# forms; the model derives "X's" from an attested stem X at a fraction of
# the stem's frequency (EngineConfig.possessiveFrequencyFraction). The
# sacred asymmetry: an UNATTESTED skeleton ("childrens", "watsons") may
# auto-restore; a VALID plural ("cats") gets the possessive as an offer at
# most — a derived possessive can never clear the skeleton-collision
# dominance gate (it has no en.lex attestation), so auto-apply past the
# valid-word rule is structurally impossible.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

SCENARIO childrens restores children's in an english lane
T "they wanted to see the "
EXPECT_POSTERIOR_LT 0.35
T childrens
EXPECT_AUTOCORRECT children's

SCENARIO watsons restores the possessive of an attested name
T "they wanted to see the "
T watsons
EXPECT_AUTOCORRECT watson's

SCENARIO cats is never rewritten to the possessive
T "they wanted to see the "
T cats
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT
EXPECT_CONTAINS cat's
T " "
EXPECT_LAST_COMMIT cats

SCENARIO typed possessive of an attested stem is valid
T "the "
T world's
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT
T " "
EXPECT_LAST_COMMIT world's

# en.lex v4: the curated contraction list now covers the full common
# inventory (they'd, haven't, he's, who's, would've, …) at repaired
# conditional-probability frequencies.
SCENARIO theyd restores they'd
T "and then "
T theyd
EXPECT_AUTOCORRECT they'd

# "shed"/"wed" are CONTRACTION_SKELETON_FOLD_EXEMPT in build-lexicon.py:
# real independent words whose frequency must not be folded into she'd/we'd
# — with their genuine counts intact, the restoration dominance gate (10x)
# can never fire on them.
SCENARIO shed never restores to she'd
T "they built a "
T shed
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT
T " "
EXPECT_LAST_COMMIT shed

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Space-miss splits: interior capitalization (2026-07-16 space_miss wave)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# A merged pair keeps the user's interior capitalization — the second
# half's first letter takes the case of the typed character it starts from
# ("RitaHayworth" → "Rita Hayworth", never "Rita hayworth").
SCENARIO merged pair keeps interior capitalization
T "and sanctuaries conway "
T SouthCarolina
EXPECT_AUTOCORRECT South Carolina

# A substitution split may never consume a SHIFTED letter as the missed
# space: uppercase is deliberate input ("ThemMangalore" must not eat the
# second M and auto-apply "Them bangalore").
SCENARIO substitution split never consumes a shifted letter
T "the priest of "
T ThemMangalore
EXPECT_NO_AUTOCORRECT

# ============================================================
# Personal surface casing (live session 2026-07-16: the bar offered
# "MEÐ"/"NEW" mid-sentence). An all-caps LEARNED surface of a word that
# is also base-lexicon vocabulary is an autocap/caps-lock artifact of
# the learning event — pipeline casing wins. Genuine acronyms are OOV
# and keep their learned caps.
# ============================================================

SCENARIO all caps learned surface of base vocabulary keeps pipeline casing
PERSONAL MEÐ 10
T "hef séð me"
EXPECT_CONTAINS með
EXPECT_NOT_CONTAINS MEÐ

SCENARIO all caps learned acronym keeps its caps
PERSONAL XYZK 10
T "skoða xyz"
EXPECT_CONTAINS XYZK
